snippet: In Florida, the governor and lawmakers have made it harder for residents to get the cheapest rates under the insurance exchange and to get help from specially trained counselors.
abstract: Florida Gov Rick Scott and Republican-dominated Legislature are making it more difficult for state residents to obtain cheapest insurance rates under insurance exchanges designed to make health care more affordable; Missouri and Ohio have also moved to undercut Affordable Care Act and its insurance exchanges.

byline.original: By LIZETTE ALVAREZ and ROBERT PEAR
byline.contributor: Lizette Alvarez reported from Miami, and Robert Pear from Washington.

lead_paragraph: In Florida, the governor and lawmakers have made it harder for residents to get the cheapest rates under the insurance exchange and to get help from specially trained counselors.

headline.main: Florida Among States Undercutting Health Care Enrollment
headline.print_headline: Several States Undercutting Health Care Enrollment
